===== theme-templates\clean-theme\README.md =====
    1: # PayIncus Clean Theme
    2: 
    3: This is the official theme sample for the PayIncus theme system.
    4: 
    5: It demonstrates:
    6: 
    7: - `payincus.theme.json` manifest validation.
    8: - Local CSS entrypoint.
    9: - Design tokens.
   10: - `configSchema` groups, ordering, color/select/text/file/placeholder fields.
   11: - Safe template fragments for public, market, user dashboard/wallet/tickets, extension center, admin dashboard banner/widgets, and shared slots.
   12: - A visual-only package boundary: no scripts, backend actions, plugin capabilities, forms, iframes, or remote URLs.
   13: 
   14: Package it with:
   15: 
   16: ```bash
   17: cd theme-templates/clean-theme
   18: tar -czf payincus-clean-theme.tar.gz payincus.theme.json README.md dist tokens templates docs
   19: ```
   20: 
   21: Then upload it in the admin Extension Center theme tab, preview it, enable it, and roll back to the default theme when needed.
===== theme-templates\clean-theme\docs\usage.md =====
    1: # PayIncus Clean Theme Usage
    2: 
    3: The Clean Theme demonstrates a visual-only PayIncus theme package. It is loaded through `GET /api/themes/active` after an administrator uploads, previews, enables, or rolls back the theme from the admin theme page.
    4: 
    5: The package includes:
    6: 
    7: - `payincus.theme.json`
    8: - `dist/theme.css`
    9: - `tokens/colors.json`
   10: - safe template fragments under `templates/`
   11: - controlled config fields declared by `configSchema`
   12: 
   13: It covers these template slots:
   14: 
   15: - `public.home.hero`
   16: - `public.home.sections`
   17: - `public.market.banner`
   18: - `public.auth.aside`
   19: - `user.shell.brand`
   20: - `user.dashboard.banner`
   21: - `user.dashboard.cards`
   22: - `user.instance.detail.extra`
   23: - `user.wallet.banner`
   24: - `user.tickets.banner`
   25: - `user.extensions.banner`
   26: - `user.orders.banner`
   27: - `user.profile.banner`
   28: - `user.invites.banner`
   29: - `user.hosts.banner`
   30: - `user.host.create.banner`
   31: - `admin.shell.brand`
   32: - `admin.extensions.header`
   33: - `admin.extensions.market.banner`
   34: - `admin.extensions.theme.banner`
   35: - `admin.dashboard.banner`
   36: - `admin.dashboard.widgets`
   37: - `admin.billing.banner`
   38: - `admin.payment.providers.banner`
   39: - `admin.oauth.banner`
   40: - `shared.footer`
   41: 
   42: Package it with:
   43: 
   44: ```bash
   45: tar -czf payincus-clean-theme.tar.gz payincus.theme.json README.md dist tokens templates docs
   46: ```
   47: 
   48: Theme packages can change CSS variables, local assets, safe HTML fragments, and admin-managed config values. They cannot run scripts, submit forms, load iframes, reference remote URLs, bypass permissions, mutate billing, or alter resource delivery logic.
